OL,6,FThe Government has scrapped its
OL,7,Fcontroversial Schools Bill as part of
OL,8,Fefforts to focus on the effects of the
OL,9,Fcurrent economic crisis.
OL,11,FThe Bill, launched in May, formed part
OL,12,Fof Boris Johnson's drive to have all
OL,13,Fschools in England join an academy
OL,14,Ftrust by 2030, and included the
OL,15,Fprovision of a new register for
OL,16,Fchildren who are homeschooled.
OL,18,FThe legislation would also have granted
OL,19,Fmore powers to Ofsted, the schools
OL,20,Finspector.
OL,3,CGovernment scraps Schools Bill to focus
OL,4,Con tackling cost of living crisis
